PART 6: The Initialization Controller
    
    This is the execution block. It is the engine starter.

    JavaScript
    document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
        runTypewriterSequence();
        fetchGitHubProjects(); // Assuming this is defined elsewhere in your file
        observeStaticCards();
        initTabSlider();
        initScrollEngine(); 
        initScrollHint(); 
        renderSocialHandles(); 
    });
    
    DOMContentLoaded: This event fires only when the HTML document has been completely parsed by the browser.

    Architectural purpose: If the script attempts to attach an Intersection Observer or a Click Listener to a button before the browser has
     finished rendering that button, the script will return undefined and fatally crash. By placing this block at the absolute end of the file
      and wrapping all function calls inside it, the engineer guarantees the DOM exists before the logic attempts to manipulate it.